Dorsal fin with 3 simple and 7 ½ branched rays. Anal fin with 3 simple and 5 ½ branched rays. Caudal fin with 9 + 8 branched rays. Pectoral fin with 14–15 rays and pelvic fin with seven rays. Body covered by scales. No scales on pectoral-fin base and on breast in front of a line connecting the base of the left and right last pectoral-fin ray (
Fig. 6
). 39 + 2 ( 4 ) or 40 + 2 ( 1 ) scales along lateral line, 16–18 irregularly set predorsal scales, ½ 3 / 1 / 3 ½ scale rows on caudal peduncle and 16 circumpeduncular scales, 4 ½ scale rows between lateral line and pelvic-fin origin and 4 ½ scale rows between lateral line and anal-fin origin. Four scale rows between anus and anal-fin origin. Barbel reaching vertical through middle of eye. Mouth strongly arched. Postlabial groove broadly interrupted medially. Upper lip thin, lower lip swollen, with a constriction at level of interruption of postlabial groove defining a lateral lobe on each side (
Fig. 6
).
